\section*{Appendix}\lvm Level 4 provides the most representative of the
examples of singular states considered in the text, since there exists the
`difficult' $\{{1\over2},{1\over2}\}$-state along with the $\{{3\over2},0\}$
and $\{0,{3\over2}\}$ ones. All the three topological singular vectors at
level 4 can be derived from the following `prototype' state {\tenpt\xpt
\BE\new\BA{l}\biggl(36(135-54\ctop+7\ctop^2+30\htop+58\ctop\htop)\cH_{-4}
